theorem
Th6: (( L1 + L2 ) is LINEAR & ( L1 - L2 ) is LINEAR)
proof
consider g1 such that A1: (for p holds ( L1 . p ) = ( g1 * p )) by CKB7:def 1;
consider g2 such that A2: (for p holds ( L2 . p ) = ( g2 * p )) by CKB7:def 1;
A3: (L1 is  total & L2 is  total) by CKB7:def 1;
now
let p;
thus ( ( L1 + L2 ) . p ) = ( ( L1 . p ) + ( L2 . p ) ) by A3,RFUNCT_1:56
.= ( ( g1 * p ) + ( L2 . p ) ) by A1
.= ( ( g1 * p ) + ( g2 * p ) ) by A2
.= ( ( g1 + g2 ) * p );
end;
hence ( L1 + L2 ) is LINEAR by A3,CKB7:def 1;
now
let p;
thus ( ( L1 - L2 ) . p ) = ( ( L1 . p ) - ( L2 . p ) ) by A3,RFUNCT_1:56
.= ( ( g1 * p ) - ( L2 . p ) ) by A1
.= ( ( g1 * p ) - ( g2 * p ) ) by A2
.= ( ( g1 - g2 ) * p );
end;
hence thesis by A3,CKB7:def 1;
end;
